The app misleadingly claims "volume booster effect" that "can also increase the volume". In fact it does not have real pre-amp capability, unlike other equalizers with pre-amp that actually add volume on top of what your phone is capable of. The volume controls merely turn up the phone's volume the way the volume-up button does. As we all know from experience with inadequate volume on phones, when you turn the volume up, the quality of the sound gets muddy rapidly once you go past the half-way point. (If I have overlooked a control for pre-amp, please point this out and I will change the review.) Also, bass boosting only decreases the treble in favor of more bass--it does not actually add any bass. On a positive note, the EQ settings have a good effect. Some reviewers have complained that the volume is reduced when you turn the EQ on. No, that's an auditory illusion--it actually goes from the phone's flat, unmusical sound to one with more quality based on the EQ settings.
